      • getXincoCoreGroups

        public List<Object> getXincoCoreGroups()
        Gets the value of the xincoCoreGroups property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the xincoCoreGroups property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getXincoCoreGroups().add(newItem);
